---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

const article = { author: "Maine Dispensary Guide Editorial Team", publishDate: "2026-01-22", modifiedDate: "2026-03-24", section: "Compliance & Legal" };
export const title = "Cannabis Edibles Compliance";
---

<Layout 
  title="Cannabis Edibles Compliance | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Maine cannabis edibles compliance guide. OCP packaging rules, THC limits, labeling requirements, and food safety standards for 2026."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1610484826967-09c5720778c7?q=80&w=2071&auto=format&fit=crop"
  article={article}
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Cannabis Edibles Compliance</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Navigating Maine's regulations for cannabis edibles and infused products</p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>The edibles market represents one of the fastest-growing segments in cannabis—and Maine's regulations ensure that these products are safe, properly labeled, and handled with the care they deserve. Whether you're manufacturing gummies, chocolates, beverages, or baked goods, understanding these rules helps you enter this exciting market the right way. Before moving forward, familiarize yourself with the <a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-license/">licensing process</a> essential for success.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Excellence in Compliance" type="success">
      Mastering this aspect of your business is a badge of professional excellence. It ensures longevity and demonstrates your commitment to the highest standards of the Maine cannabis industry.
    </Callout>


    <section>
      <h2>License Requirements</h2>
      <p>Under <a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maine OCP regulations</a>, producing edibles requires:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Products Manufacturing License</strong> — Required for creating infused products</li>
        <li>Compliant manufacturing facility</li>
        <li>Proper food safety certifications</li>
        <li>Employee food handler training</li>
        <li>Approved testing laboratory partnership</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Edibles Categories</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Confections</strong> — Gummies, chocolates, hard candies</li>
        <li><strong>Baked Goods</strong> — Brownies, cookies, baked treats</li>
        <li><strong>Beverages</strong> — Infused drinks, teas, coffees</li>
        <li><strong>Tinctures</strong> — Sublingual products</li>
        <li><strong>Topicals</strong> — Lotions, balms with infused cannabinoids</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Packaging & Labeling</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Child-resistant <a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-packaging/">packaging</a> required</li>
        <li>Clear potency labeling (THC per serving)</li>
        <li>Ingredient lists</li>
        <li>Allergen warnings</li>
        <li>Serving size information</li>
        <li>Mandatory warnings</li>
        <li>No appealing to children</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Manufacturing Standards</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Follow food safety regulations</li>
        <li>Maintain clean production environment</li>
        <li>Document all production batches</li>
        <li>Test each batch before sale</li>
        <li>Properly store ingredients</li>
        <li>Implement quality control processes</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Investment</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Category</th><th>Estimated Cost</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Manufacturing License</td><td>$5,000-15,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Facility Build-out</td><td>$50,000-200,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Equipment</td><td>$30,000-100,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Testing</td><td>$500-2,000/batch</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Further Reading</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maine Cannabis Rules</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>This is for informational purposes only and does not constitute legal or financial advice. Consult with qualified professionals.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
</style>
